'''Ramiz Larbi Zerrouki''' ({{Langx|ar|رامز العربي زروقي}}; born 26 May 1998) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{Dutch football updater|Twente}} club [[FC Twente|Twente]], on loan from [[Feyenoord]], and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

==Club career==
===Twente===
====Youth years (2008–18)====
Born in [[Amsterdam]],<ref name="Tub1">{{cite news |last1=Voorde |first1=Leon ten |title=Van Amsterdam naar Haaksbergen: op bezoek bij Ramiz Zerrouki in zijn gastgezin in Twente |url=https://www.tubantia.nl/fc-twente/van-amsterdam-naar-haaksbergen-op-bezoek-bij-ramiz-zerrouki-in-zijn-gastgezin-in-twente~a75530c9/ |access-date=23 January 2024 |work=Tubantia |date=5 May 2023 |language=nl}}</ref> Zerrouki started playing football for at the [[Ajax Youth Academy]]. However, in 2016, he decided to join the [[FC Twente|Twente]] football academy, and became a resident with a host family, namely former Twente player [[Marcel Mentink]] and his wife, Birgit.<ref name="Tub1" />

During the 2017–18 season, he gained experience with the reserve team [[Jong FC Twente|Jong Twente]] in the fourth-tier [[Derde Divisie]], where he netted his only goal in a 3–0 away victory against [[Harkemase Boys]]. From the 2018–19 season onwards, he continued his development with Jong Twente in the reserves' team league, the [[Beloften Eredivisie]]. In August 2018, he signed his first professional contract with Twente, which eventually led to his promotion to the first-team squad in the summer of 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Talenten FC Twente tekenen contract |url=https://www.fctwente.nl/club/nieuws/talenten-fc-twente-tekenen-contract |website=[[FC Twente]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200910185836/https://www.fctwente.nl/club/nieuws/talenten-fc-twente-tekenen-contract |archive-date=10 September 2020 |language=nl |date=8 August 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

====First team (2020–23)====
Zerrouki made his first-team debut for Twente on 30 October 2019, during a [[KNVB Cup]] match against [[De Treffers]], which they won 2–0. Under coach [[Gonzalo García (footballer, born 1983)|Gonzalo García]], he made a brief appearance, replacing [[Queensy Menig]] in the 89th minute.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Voorde |first1=Leon ten |title=Gewonnen bekerduel FC Twente kwam geen moment tot leven |url=https://www.tubantia.nl/fc-twente/gewonnen-bekerduel-fc-twente-kwam-geen-moment-tot-leven~acfe9ff0/ |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Tubantia |date=31 October 2019 |language=nl}}</ref> However, he struggled to secure more opportunities under García and mostly trained with a smaller group at the Twente reserves, led by coach [[Theo ten Caat]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Voorde |first1=Leon ten |title=Van niet gezien tot uitblinker: Zerrouki en Wieffer tellen nu wel mee |url=https://www.tubantia.nl/fc-twente/van-niet-gezien-tot-uitblinker-zerrouki-en-wieffer-tellen-nu-wel-mee~ab152401/ |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Tubantia |date=18 February 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

Despite the initial challenges, his contract was extended in March 2020, keeping him at the club until 30 June 2021. In the run-up to the [[2020–21 FC Twente season|2020–21 season]], Zerrouki caught the eye of the new coach, [[Ron Jans]]. As a result, he began to receive regular playing time from the start of the season, and in October 2020, he extended his contract until 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ramiz Zerrouki verlengt contract: "Ben op mijn plek hier" |url=https://www.fctwente.nl/club/nieuws/ramiz-zerrouki-verlengt-contract-ben-op-mijn-plek-hier |website=FC Twente |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508102129/https://www.fctwente.nl/club/nieuws/ramiz-zerrouki-verlengt-contract-ben-op-mijn-plek-hier |archive-date=8 May 2021 |language=nl |date=19 October 2020 |url-status=dead}}</ref> His determination and dedication paid off, and he secured a spot in the starting lineup following an injury to [[Wout Brama]] after the winter break.<ref>{{cite news |title=FC Twente zonder Brama, Zerrouki en Ugalde tegen NEC |url=https://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/2020989/fc-twente-zonder-brama-zerrouki-en-ugalde-tegen-nec |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=RTV Oost |date=22 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022165116/https://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/2020989/FC-Twente-zonder-Brama-Zerrouki-en-Ugalde-tegen-NEC |archive-date=22 October 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

In the [[2021–22 FC Twente season|2021–22 season]], Zerrouki marked his presence by scoring his first goals for Twente. He played a crucial role in their 2–0 cup victory against [[OSS '20]] on 27 October 2021, where he scored both goals.<ref>{{cite news |title=FC Twente wint bekerpotje bij O.S.S.'20 dankzij Ramiz Zerrouki |url=https://sportnieuws.nl/voetbal/binnenland/fc-twente-wint-bekerpotje-bij-o-s-s-20-dankzij-beauty-ramiz-zerrouki/ |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Sportnieuws.nl |date=27 October 2021 |language=nl}}</ref> Just three days later, he found the back of the net again, this time in a league match against [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ottens |first1=Chris |title=PSV speelt chagrijn van zich af tegen FC Twente, Vinícius is eindelijk los |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/psv-speelt-chagrijn-van-zich-af-tegen-fc-twente-vinicius-is-eindelijk-los~adf9a0aa/ |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Algemeen Dagblad |date=30 October 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

In March 2022, Ramiz Zerrouki's commitment to Twente was further solidified when he extended his contract with the club until 2024, with an option for the club to extend the agreement for an additional year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zerrouki zet handtekening onder nieuw Twente-contract |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/zerrouki-zet-handtekening-onder-nieuw-twente-contract |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Voetbal International |date=17 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220826093432/https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/zerrouki-zet-handtekening-onder-nieuw-twente-contract |archive-date=26 August 2022 |language=nl}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===
In the summer of 2022, [[Feyenoord]] expressed interest in Zerrouki, but a transfer did not materialise. This situation persisted during the winter transfer window of [[2022–23 Eredivisie|2022–23]] when both clubs failed to reach an agreement. However, in June 2023, they did reach an agreement, and Zerrouki signed a four-year contract with Feyenoord.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ramiz Zerrouki zet handtekening bij Feyenoord: 'Een last die van mijn schouders valt' |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/ramiz-zerrouki-zet-handtekening-bij-feyenoord-een-last-die-van-mijn-schouders-valt~a23f4360e/ |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=Algemeen Dagblad |date=22 June 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

Zerrouki made his debut for the club on 4 August, starting in a 1–0 loss to rivals [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] in the [[Johan Cruyff Shield]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gouka |first1=Mikos |title=PSV verslaat Feyenoord in de Kuip: Noa Lang beslist strijd om Johan Cruijff Schaal |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/johan-cruijff-schaal-psv-feyenoord~a4c423ad/ |access-date=2 October 2023 |work=Algemeen Dagblad |date=4 August 2023 |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Feyenoord vs. PSV 0–1: Summary |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/08/04/netherlands/super-cup/feyenoord-rotterdam-nv/psv-nv/4075675/ |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=2 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231002161323/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/08/04/netherlands/super-cup/feyenoord-rotterdam-nv/psv-nv/4075675/ |archive-date=2 October 2023}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Feyenoord on 25 October, contributing to a 3–1 home victory against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] in the [[UEFA Champions League]] group phase.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fenomenaal Feyenoord: Zerrouki scoort prachtig, Lazio wordt overklast |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/videos/1158547/fenomenaal-feyenoord-zerrouki-scoort-prachtig-lazio-wordt-overklast.html |access-date=27 June 2024 |work=VoetbalPrimeur.nl |date=25 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030013525/https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/videos/1158547/fenomenaal-feyenoord-zerrouki-scoort-prachtig-lazio-wordt-overklast.html |archive-date=30 October 2023 |language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Feyenoord – Lazio Roma 3:1 (Champions League 2023/2024, Group E) |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma9909818/lineup/ |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=27 June 2024 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240508113807/https://www.worldfootball.net/report/champions-league-2023-2024-gruppe-e-feyenoord-lazio-roma/ |archive-date=8 May 2024}}</ref> Zerrouki played regularly during his first season at the club, scoring once in 36 appearances in all competitions, as Feyenoord [[2023–24 KNVB Cup|won]] the [[KNVB Cup]] and finished second in the Eredivisie.<ref name="SW" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Feyenoord wint voor de veertiende keer TOTO KNVB Beker |url=https://www.totoknvbbeker.nl/nieuws/toto-knvb-beker/feyenoord-wint-voor-de-veertiende-keer-toto-knvb-beker |access-date=27 June 2024 |work=TOTO KNVB Beker |date=21 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240422144742/https://www.totoknvbbeker.nl/nieuws/toto-knvb-beker/feyenoord-wint-voor-de-veertiende-keer-toto-knvb-beker |archive-date=22 April 2024 |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Feyenoord heeft Champions League-ticket definitief binnen na 'topseizoen' |url=https://eredivisie.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-verzekert-zich-na-topseizoen-van-champions-league-voetbal/ |access-date=27 June 2024 |work=Eredivisie |date=26 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240627190207/https://eredivisie.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-verzekert-zich-na-topseizoen-van-champions-league-voetbal/ |archive-date=27 June 2024 |language=nl}}</ref>

====Loan to Twente====
On 30 July 2025, Zerrouki re‑joined [[FC Twente|Twente]] on a season‑long loan, remaining at [[De Grolsch Veste]] until the end of the [[2025–26 Eredivisie|2025–26 campaign]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ramiz Zerrouki voor één seizoen terug bij FC Twente |url=https://fctwente.nl/nieuws/ramiz-zerrouki-voor-een-seizoen-naar-fc-twente |website=FC Twente |access-date=30 July 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250730112133/https://fctwente.nl/nieuws/ramiz-zerrouki-voor-een-seizoen-naar-fc-twente |archive-date=30 July 2025 |language=nl-NL |date=30 July 2025 |trans-title=Ramiz Zerrouki returns to FC Twente for one season}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ramiz Zerrouki verhuurd aan FC Twente |url=https://www.feyenoord.com/nl/news/ramiz-zerrouki-verhuurd-aan-fc-twente-300725 |website=Feyenoord |access-date=30 July 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250730153501/https://www.feyenoord.com/nl/news/ramiz-zerrouki-verhuurd-aan-fc-twente-300725 |archive-date=30 July 2025 |language=nl |date=30 July 2025 |trans-title=Ramiz Zerrouki loaned to FC Twente}}</ref>

==International career==
Zerrouki was born in the Netherlands and is Algerian by descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://alkhaleejtoday.co/sport/5139114/Twente-breaks-open-contract-of-revelation-%E2%80%98interesting-player-for-the-future%E2%80%99.html |title=Twente breaks open contract of revelation: 'interesting player for the future' |date=19 October 2020 |website=AlKhaleej Today}}</ref> He had his debut with the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]] in a 3–3 [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] tie with [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] on 25 March 2021.<ref name="Strack-Zimmermann 2021">{{cite web | last=Strack-Zimmermann | first=Benjamin | title=Zambia vs. Algeria (3:3) | website=National Football Teams | date=25 March 2021 | url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/30275/Zambia_Algeria.html | access-date=29 March 2021}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Algeria on 2 September 2021 against [[Djibouti national football team|Djibouti]] scoring the eighth goal of the game.

He was included in Algeria's squad for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Africa Cup of Nations 2021 squads |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59698987 |access-date=4 November 2023 |work=BBC Sport |date=8 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030200344/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59698987 |archive-date=30 October 2023}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in Algeria's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.algerie-focus.com/can-2024-lalgerie-devoile-sa-liste-officielle-qui-sont-les-fennecs-prets-a-conquerir-lafrique/|title=CAN 2024 : L'Algérie Dévoile sa Liste Officielle – Qui Sont les Fennecs Prêts à Conquérir l'Afrique ?|language=French|date=30 December 2023|access-date=12 January 2024|publisher=Algérie-Focus}}</ref>

